        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 4:02PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Yosemite National, or 12 miles north of Yosemite South Entrance,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Yosemite Valley, Yosemite National, Tamarack Flat Campground, Little
Yosemite Valley Campground, Badger Pass Ranger Station, Morraine Dome
Campground, Camp 4 Campground, North Pines Campground, Yosemite
Glacier Point, Ostrander Lake, Bridalveil Creek Campground, Little
Yosemite Valley Ranger Station, Crane Flat Campground, Yosemite
Valley Vistor Center, Lower Pines Campground, and Upper Pines
Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
